-- vision.fl — Multimodal image analysis
-- Demonstrates: load image, multi-provider vision, comparison
-- Usage: fluent run examples/vision.fl
-- Requires: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY and/or OPENAI_API_KEY

-- ── Load a local image ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- Replace this path with any image file on your system.
-- Supported formats: JPG, PNG, WEBP, GIF, BMP
Let photo be load image "examples/assets/sample.jpg".

Output "=== Vision Analysis Pipeline ===".
Output "".

-- ── Describe the image (Claude) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
@model(temperature: 0.3, max_tokens: 300)
Ask claude to "Describe what you see in this image in detail. Note objects, people, text, colours, and any notable elements." using image photo and call the result claude_description.

Output "Claude sees:".
Output claude_description.
Output "".

-- ── Extract any visible text (OpenAI GPT-4o Vision) ─────────────────────────
@model(temperature: 0, max_tokens: 200)
Ask openai/gpt-4o to "Extract every piece of visible text from this image. If there is no text, say 'No text found'." using image photo and call the result visible_text.

Output "Visible text (GPT-4o):".
Output visible_text.
Output "".

-- ── Classify mood/tone (Gemini) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
@model(temperature: 0.2, max_tokens: 100)
Ask gemini to "In one sentence, describe the mood or atmosphere of this image." using image photo and call the result mood.

Output "Mood (Gemini):".
Output mood.
Output "".

-- ── Cross-model synthesis ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@model(temperature: 0.3, max_tokens: 200)
Ask claude to "Given these three analyses of the same image, write a single unified summary." using data a record with description claude_description text visible_text atmosphere mood and call the result final_summary.

Output "=== Final Synthesis ===".
Output final_summary.
